Cheers!

<b>Summer</b>

<i>The Greyhound</i>
<ul>
	<li>6 oz. Schöfferhofer Grapefruit</li>
	<li>1.5 oz. vodka or gin</li>
	<li>Salt the rim and you’ve got yourself a “Salty Dog” instead</li>
</ul>
<i>The Campari Radler</i> (taken from <a href="http://www.151nyc.com/">151</a> in New York City)
<ul>
	<li>8 oz. Schöfferhofer Grapefruit</li>
	<li>1 oz. Campari</li>
	<li>¼ oz. lemon juice</li>
</ul>
<i>The Paloma</i>
<ul>
	<li>3 oz. Schöfferhofer Grapefruit</li>
	<li>3 oz. tequila</li>
	<li>½ oz. lime juice</li>
</ul>
<i>The Grapefruit Lime Spritzer</i>
<ul>
	<li>8 oz. Schöfferhofer Grapefruit</li>
	<li>3 oz. vodka</li>
	<li>1.5 oz. triple sec</li>
	<li>1 oz. lime juice</li>
	<li>4 oz. club soda</li>
</ul>
A take on <i>The Drive Away</i>
<ul>
	<li>3 oz. Schöfferhofer Grapefruit</li>
	<li>½ oz. dark rum</li>
	<li>½ oz. amaretto</li>
	<li>2 oz. orange juice</li>
</ul>
<b>Fall</b>

<i>The Mexican Greyhound</i>
<ul>
	<li>6 oz. Schöfferhofer Grapefruit</li>
	<li>1.5 oz. mezcal</li>
	<li>Salted rim</li>
</ul>
A take on <i>The New Brunswick </i>(inspired by Maggie Hoffman’s <a href="http://www.seriouseats.com/recipes/2012/12/new-brunswick-cocktail-grapefruit-rye-recipe.html">recipe</a> at Serious Eats)
<ul>
	<li>3 oz. Schöfferhofer Grapefruit</li>
	<li>1.5 oz. rye whiskey</li>
	<li>1 oz. sweet vermouth</li>
	<li>¼ oz. lemon juice</li>
	<li>2 dashes grapefruit bitters</li>
</ul>
