The Growler Collar serves a simple purpose - helping to clean, drain and dry 32 oz. and 64 oz. growlers. As you can see in the photo above, the Growler Collar screws onto the growler, creating a stable base when flipped upside-down. If you're reading this, I'll just assume you have a growler or two and understand exactly what I'm talking about - you wash them easily enough and then create a precarious setup to prop them upside-down, hoping the entire time that they don't fall over and break. The simple threaded design allows the Growler Collar to screw onto standard brown glass growlers, forever ensuring your precious jugs won't ever end up in pieces on the floor. Check one out in action <a href="https://vimeo.com/112858411" target="_blank">here</a>.

The Growler Collar only runs $10 and can be purchased <a href="http://www.growlercollar.com/Craft_Artisan_Beer_Growler_PurchaseAGrowlerCollar.html" target="_blank">here</a>. You probably won't find these in stores anytime soon, so I definitely suggest heading to the website and purchasing a couple. 10% of the proceeds go to local, regional, national and international aid/ mission trips each year, so you can feel good about your purchase too. Plus, anything that makes it easier to use a growler means less waste, so you're helping out the environment as well.

Cheers!

P.S. If you're a bar or brewery owner, you can get <a href="http://www.growlercollar.com/Craft_Artisan_Beer_Growler_CustomImprints.html" target="_blank">custom Growler Collars</a> in 24 colors with your logo on them as well.

