But I’m not writing about New Glarus to kiss Carey ass. I’m writing about them because I think Chicago is close enough to New Glarus to make for a fantastic weekend getaway. New Glarus, WI is <a href="https://www.google.com/maps/dir/Chicago,+IL/New+Glarus,+WI/@42.3520685,-89.2238301,9z/data=!4m13!4m12!1m5!1m1!1s0x880e2c3cd0f4cbed:0xafe0a6ad09c0c000!2m2!1d-87.6297982!2d41.8781136!1m5!1m1!1s0x8807c130983461e3:0x99e986b2bcd536ce!2m2!1d-89.6351217!2d42.8144473" target="_blank">just 150 miles</a> from Chicago – an easy 3 hour drive away (or quicker if you drive like most Illinoans). Swiss heritage abounds in the quaint town and New Glarus beer flows freely.

So if you’re a beer lover looking to get away from the big lights and busy streets, you should seriously consider <a href="http://www.newglarusbrewing.com/index.cfm/ourtown/map" target="_blank">New Glarus, WI</a>. I can promise you won’t be disappointed just like I can promise you’ll have friends hitting you up to bring New Glarus beer back for them.

Cheers!

